Neural ICE OTA trust anchors (ICE-Fabric OTA signing plan — P0)
===============================================================================

This directory holds the PUBLIC keys the appliance uses to verify signed OTA
update bundles before applying them. The keys are staged here at the Owner key
ceremony (P0) — they are NOT generated by, or shipped from, this repository:

  ota-root.pub   OTA root key (offline, hardware-token-held). Under ADR-0039 it
                 verifies complete delegation snapshots and exact delegated-key
                 emergency recovery only. Root-anchor rotation requires a
                 separately approved image/trust-anchor transition; this gate
                 deliberately rejects it. The root never signs routine BOMs,
                 release envelopes or channel assignments.

  image-ci.pub   Legacy direct image-key staging location. Delegated v2 obtains
                 the current image-ci public key and exact role/scope from the
                 accepted root-signed snapshot; the immutable root remains the
                 trust anchor.

Only public keys ever live here. Private keys never touch the device or this
repository.

Behavior of the on-device verifier (`ni-ota-verify`, P2) when a key file is
missing or empty:

  - delegated authenticity, role/scope, target, time and anti-rollback failures
    always REFUSE, including when enforce=0;
  - enforce=0 affects only explicitly non-authoritative rollout observations;
  - enforce=1 refuses every failed check.
